verbose_text: In people and dogs with serotonin syndrome, tremors, hyperreflexia, spontaneous clonus, and muscle rigidity could all contribute to release of CK.1, 12 As such, the increase in ALT, AST, and CK observed in the patient reported here could have been secondary to a combination of hepatocellular injury induced by xylitol, and muscle activity secondary to serotonin like syndrome.
